Preconditions:
- The input array `ratings` is not null.
- The length of the input array `ratings` is greater than 0.
- The elements in the input array `ratings` are non-negative integers.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer representing the minimum number of candies needed to distribute to the children.
- Each child has at least one candy.
- Children with a higher rating have more candies than their neighbors.